### Basic Data types

Redis supports 5 basic data types

## Redis String command{.cols-3}

### APPEND

```{.wrap}
APPEND key value

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> EXISTS mykey
(integer) 0
redis> APPEND mykey "Hello"
(integer) 5
redis> APPEND mykey " World"
(integer) 11
redis> GET mykey
"Hello World"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Append a value to a key

### BITCOUNT

```{.wrap}
BITCOUNT key [start end]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SET mykey "foobar"
"OK"
redis> BITCOUNT mykey
(integer) 26
redis> BITCOUNT mykey 0 0
(integer) 4
redis> BITCOUNT mykey 1 1
(integer) 6

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Count set bits in a string

### BITFIELD

```{.wrap}
BITFIELD key [GET type offset] [SET type offset value] [INCRBY type offset increment] [OVERFLOW WRAP|SAT|FAIL]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> BITFIELD mykey INCRBY i5 100 1 GET u4 0
1) (integer) 1
2) (integer) 0

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Perform arbitrary bitfield integer operations on strings

### BITOP

```{.wrap}
BITOP operation destkey key [key ...]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SET key1 "foobar"
"OK"
redis> SET key2 "abcdef"
"OK"
redis> BITOP AND dest key1 key2
(integer) 6
redis> GET dest
"`bc`ab"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Perform bitwise operations between strings

### BITPOS

```{.wrap}
BITPOS key bit [start] [end]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SET mykey "\xff\xf0\x00"
"OK"
redis> BITPOS mykey 0
(integer) 12
redis> SET mykey "\x00\xff\xf0"
"OK"
redis> BITPOS mykey 1 0
(integer) 8
redis> BITPOS mykey 1 2
(integer) 16
redis> set mykey "\x00\x00\x00"
"OK"
redis> BITPOS mykey 1
(integer) -1

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Find first bit set or clear in a string

### DECR

```{.wrap}
DECR key

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SET mykey "10"
"OK"
redis> DECR mykey
(integer) 9
redis> SET mykey "234293482390480948029348230948"
"OK"
redis> DECR mykey
ERR ERR value is not an integer or out of range

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Decrement the integer value of a key by one

### DECRBY

```{.wrap}
DECRBY key decrement

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SET mykey "10"
"OK"
redis> DECRBY mykey 3
(integer) 7

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Decrement the integer value of a key by the given number

### GET

```{.wrap}
GET key

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> GET nonexisting
(nil)
redis> SET mykey "Hello"
"OK"
redis> GET mykey
"Hello"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Get the value of a key

### GETBIT

```{.wrap}
GETBIT key offset

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SETBIT mykey 7 1
(integer) 0
redis> GETBIT mykey 0
(integer) 0
redis> GETBIT mykey 7
(integer) 1
redis> GETBIT mykey 100
(integer) 0

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Returns the bit value at offset in the string value stored at key

### GETRANGE

```{.wrap}
GETRANGE key start end

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SET mykey "This is a string"
"OK"
redis> GETRANGE mykey 0 3
"This"
redis> GETRANGE mykey -3 -1
"ing"
redis> GETRANGE mykey 0 -1
"This is a string"
redis> GETRANGE mykey 10 100
"string"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Get a substring of the string stored at a key

### GETSET

```{.wrap}
GETSET key value

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> INCR mycounter
(integer) 1
redis> GETSET mycounter "0"
"1"
redis> GET mycounter
"0"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Set the string value of a key and return its old value

### INCR

```{.wrap}
INCR key

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SET mykey "10"
"OK"
redis> INCR mykey
(integer) 11
redis> GET mykey
"11"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Increment the integer value of a key by one

### MSETNX

```{.wrap}
MSETNX key value [key value ...]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> MSETNX key1 "Hello" key2 "there"
(integer) 1
redis> MSETNX key2 "new" key3 "world"
(integer) 0
redis> MGET key1 key2 key3
1) "Hello"
2) "there"
3) (nil)

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Set multiple keys to multiple values, only if none of the keys exist

### INCRBYFLOAT

```{.wrap}
INCRBYFLOAT key increment

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SET mykey 10.50
"OK"
redis> INCRBYFLOAT mykey 0.1
"10.6"
redis> INCRBYFLOAT mykey -5
"5.6"
redis> SET mykey 5.0e3
"OK"
redis> INCRBYFLOAT mykey 2.0e2
"5200"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Increment the float value of a key by the given amount

### MGET

```{.wrap}
MGET key [key ...]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SET key1 "Hello"
"OK"
redis> SET key2 "World"
"OK"
redis> MGET key1 key2 nonexisting
1) "Hello"
2) "World"
3) (nil)

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Get the values of all the given keys

### MSET

```{.wrap}
MSET key value [key value ...]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> MSET key1 "Hello" key2 "World"
"OK"
redis> GET key1
"Hello"
redis> GET key2
"World"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Set multiple keys to multiple values

### INCRBY

```{.wrap}
INCRBY key increment

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SET mykey "10"
"OK"
redis> INCRBY mykey 5
(integer) 15

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Increment the integer value of a key by the given amount

### PSETEX

```{.wrap}
PSETEX key milliseconds value

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> PSETEX mykey 1000 "Hello"
"OK"
redis> PTTL mykey
(integer) 1000
redis> GET mykey
"Hello"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Set the value and expiration in milliseconds of a key

### SET

```{.wrap}
SET key value [EX seconds|PX milliseconds|KEEPTTL] [NX|XX] [GET]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SET mykey "Hello"
"OK"
redis> GET mykey
"Hello"
redis> SET anotherkey "will expire in a minute" EX 60
"OK"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Set the string value of a key

### SETBIT

```{.wrap}
SETBIT key offset value

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SETBIT mykey 7 1
(integer) 0
redis> SETBIT mykey 7 0
(integer) 1
redis> GET mykey
"\u0000"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Sets or clears the bit at offset in the string value stored at key

### SETEX

```{.wrap}
SETEX key seconds value

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SETEX mykey 10 "Hello"
"OK"
redis> TTL mykey
(integer) 10
redis> GET mykey
"Hello"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Set the value and expiration of a key

### SETNX

```{.wrap}
SETNX key value

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SETNX mykey "Hello"
(integer) 1
redis> SETNX mykey "World"
(integer) 0
redis> GET mykey
"Hello"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Set the value of a key, only if the key does not exist

### SETRANGE

```{.wrap}
SETRANGE key offset value

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SET key1 "Hello World"
"OK"
redis> SETRANGE key1 6 "Redis"
(integer) 11
redis> GET key1
"Hello Redis"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Overwrite part of a string at key starting at the specified offset

### STRLEN

```{.wrap}
STRLEN key

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SET mykey "Hello world"
"OK"
redis> STRLEN mykey
(integer) 11
redis> STRLEN nonexisting
(integer) 0

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Get the length of the value stored in a key

### STRALGO

```{.wrap}
STRALGO LCS algo-specific-argument [algo-specific-argument ...]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> STRALGO LCS KEYS key1 key2 IDX
1) "matches"
2) 1) 1) 1) (integer) 4
2) (integer) 7
2) 1) (integer) 5
2) (integer) 8
2) 1) 1) (integer) 2
2) (integer) 3
2) 1) (integer) 0
2) (integer) 1
3) "len"
4) (integer) 6

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Run algorithms (currently LCS) against strings

## Redis Set command

### SADD

```{.wrap}
SADD key member [member ...]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SADD myset "Hello"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD myset "World"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD myset "World"
(integer) 0
redis> SMEMBERS myset
1) "Hello"
2) "World"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Add one or more members to a set

### SCARD

```{.wrap}
SCARD key

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SADD myset "Hello"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD myset "World"
(integer) 1
redis> SCARD myset
(integer) 2

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Get the number of members in a set

### SDIFF

```{.wrap}
SDIFF key [key ...]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SADD key1 "a"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key1 "b"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key1 "c"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key2 "c"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key2 "d"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key2 "e"
(integer) 1
redis> SDIFF key1 key2
1) "a"
2) "b"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Subtract multiple sets

### SDIFFSTORE

```{.wrap}
SDIFFSTORE destination key [key ...]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SADD key1 "a"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key1 "b"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key1 "c"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key2 "c"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key2 "d"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key2 "e"
(integer) 1
redis> SDIFFSTORE key key1 key2
(integer) 2
redis> SMEMBERS key
1) "a"
2) "b"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Subtract multiple sets and store the resulting set in a key

### SINTER

```{.wrap}
SINTER key [key ...]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SADD key1 "a"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key1 "b"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key1 "c"
(integer) 1

(integer) 1
redis> SADD key2 "d"

Intersect multiple sets

### SINTERSTORE

```{.wrap}
SINTERSTORE destination key [key ...]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SADD key1 "a"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key1 "b"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key1 "c"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key2 "c"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key2 "d"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key2 "e"
(integer) 1
redis> SINTERSTORE key key1 key2
(integer) 1
redis> SMEMBERS key
1) "c"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Intersect multiple sets and store the resulting set in a key

### SISMEMBER

```{.wrap}
SISMEMBER key member

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SADD myset "one"
(integer) 1
redis> SISMEMBER myset "one"
(integer) 1
redis> SISMEMBER myset "two"
(integer) 0

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Determine if a given value is a member of a set

### SMISMEMBER

```{.wrap}
SMISMEMBER key member [member ...]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SADD myset "one"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD myset "one"
(integer) 0
redis> SMISMEMBER myset "one" "notamember"
1) (integer) 1
2) (integer) 0

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Returns the membership associated with the given elements for a set

### SMEMBERS

```{.wrap}
SMEMBERS key

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SADD myset "Hello"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD myset "World"
(integer) 1
redis> SMEMBERS myset
1) "Hello"
2) "World"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Get all the members in a set

### SMOVE

```{.wrap}
SMOVE source destination member

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SADD myset "one"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD myset "two"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD myotherset "three"
(integer) 1
redis> SMOVE myset myotherset "two"
(integer) 1
redis> SMEMBERS myset
1) "one"
redis> SMEMBERS myotherset
1) "two"
2) "three"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Move a member from one set to another

### SPOP

```{.wrap}
SPOP key [count]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SADD myset "one"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD myset "two"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD myset "three"
(integer) 1
redis> SPOP myset
"two"
redis> SMEMBERS myset
1) "one"
2) "three"
redis> SADD myset "four"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD myset "five"
(integer) 1
redis> SPOP myset 3
1) "four"
2) "five"
3) "three"
redis> SMEMBERS myset
1) "one"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Remove and return one or multiple random members from a set

### SRANDMEMBER

```{.wrap}
SRANDMEMBER key [count]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SADD myset one two three
(integer) 3
redis> SRANDMEMBER myset
"three"
redis> SRANDMEMBER myset 2
1) "two"
2) "three"
redis> SRANDMEMBER myset -5
1) "one"
2) "two"
3) "three"
4) "three"
5) "one"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Get one or multiple random members from a set

### SREM

```{.wrap}
SREM key member [member ...]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script

(integer) 1
redis> SADD myset "two"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD myset "three"
(integer) 1
redis> SREM myset "one"
(integer) 1
redis> SREM myset "four"

redis> SMEMBERS myset

Remove one or more members from a set

### SUNION

```{.wrap}
SUNION key [key ...]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script

(integer) 1
redis> SADD key1 "b"
(integer) 1

### SUNIONSTORE

```{.wrap}
SUNIONSTORE destination key [key ...]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> SADD key1 "a"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key1 "b"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key1 "c"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key2 "c"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key2 "d"
(integer) 1
redis> SADD key2 "e"

## Redis List command

### Misc

| -                                                   | -                                                                                                  |
| --------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| [BRPOPLPUSH ](https://redis.io/commands/brpoplpush) | Pop an element from a list, push it to another list and return it; or block until one is available |
| [BLMOVE ](https://redis.io/commands/blmove)         | Pop an element from a list, push it to another list and return it; or block until one is available |

### BLPOP

```{.wrap}
BLPOP key [key ...] timeout

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> DEL list1 list2
(integer) 0
redis> RPUSH list1 a b c
(integer) 3
redis> BLPOP list1 list2 0
1) "list1"
2) "a"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Remove and get the first element in a list, or block until one is available |

### BRPOP

```{.wrap}
BRPOP key [key ...] timeout

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> DEL list1 list2
(integer) 0
redis> RPUSH list1 a b c
(integer) 3
redis> BRPOP list1 list2 0
1) "list1"
2) "c"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Remove and get the last element in a list, or block until one is available |

### LINDEX

```{.wrap}
LINDEX key index

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> LPUSH mylist "World"
(integer) 1
redis> LPUSH mylist "Hello"
(integer) 2
redis> LINDEX mylist 0
"Hello"
redis> LINDEX mylist -1
"World"
redis> LINDEX mylist 3
(nil)

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Get an element from a list by its index

### LINSERT

```{.wrap}
LINSERT key BEFORE|AFTER pivot element

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> RPUSH mylist "Hello"
(integer) 1
redis> RPUSH mylist "World"
(integer) 2
redis> LINSERT mylist BEFORE "World" "There"
(integer) 3
redis> LRANGE mylist 0 -1
1) "Hello"
2) "There"
3) "World"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Insert an element before or after another element in a list

### LLEN

```{.wrap}
LLEN key

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> LPUSH mylist "World"
(integer) 1
redis> LPUSH mylist "Hello"
(integer) 2
redis> LLEN mylist
(integer) 2

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Get the length of a list

### LPOP

```{.wrap}
LPOP key [count]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> RPUSH mylist "one"
(integer) 1
redis> RPUSH mylist "two"
(integer) 2
redis> RPUSH mylist "three"
(integer) 3
redis> LPOP mylist
"one"
redis> LRANGE mylist 0 -1
1) "two"
2) "three"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Remove and get the first elements in a list

### LPOS

```{.wrap}
LPOS key element [RANK rank] [COUNT num-matches] [MAXLEN len]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> RPUSH mylist a b c d 1 2 3 4 3 3 3
(integer) 11
redis> LPOS mylist 3
(integer) 6
redis> LPOS mylist 3 COUNT 0 RANK 2
1) (integer) 8
2) (integer) 9
3) (integer) 10

cards.title: Getting started

Return the index of matching elements on a list

### LPUSH

```{.wrap}
LPUSH key element [element ...]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> LPUSH mylist "world"
(integer) 1
redis> LPUSH mylist "hello"
(integer) 2
redis> LRANGE mylist 0 -1

2) "world"

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Prepend one or multiple elements to a list

### LPUSHX

```{.wrap}
LPUSHX key element [element ...]

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script
redis> LPUSH mylist "World"
(integer) 1
redis> LPUSHX mylist "Hello"
(integer) 2
redis> LPUSHX myotherlist "Hello"
(integer) 0
redis> LRANGE mylist 0 -1
1) "Hello"
2) "World"
redis> LRANGE myotherlist 0 -1
(empty list or set)

cards.title: Getting started
cards.code:
Prepend an element to a list, only if the list exists

### LRANGE

```{.wrap}
LRANGE key start stop

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script

(integer) 1
redis> RPUSH mylist "two"
(integer) 2
redis> RPUSH mylist "three"

Get a range of elements from a list

### LREM

```{.wrap}
LREM key count element

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script

(integer) 2

### LSET

```{.wrap}
LSET key index element

cards.title: Getting started
cards.body:
```shell script

(integer) 1
redis> RPUSH mylist "two"
